## 🧠 Prompt Engineering Tips

When asking AI assistants for help:

- Specify the LLM engineering concept clearly (e.g., "Implement a ReAct agent")
- Request multi-provider support (OpenAI + Azure OpenAI)
- Ask for multi-language examples when applicable
- Request proper experiment logging
- Specify reproducibility requirements (seeds, version logging)

## ✅ Quality Checklist

### Before Submitting Code/Notebooks

- [ ] **Kernel Restart & Run All** passes without errors
- [ ] All random processes use fixed seeds for reproducibility
- [ ] Visualizations have titles, labels, and legends
- [ ] Code comments explain the *why* (LLM engineering reasoning), not just the *how*
- [ ] Prompt templates have metadata sidecars
- [ ] Experiment logs follow standard format
- [ ] Multi-provider support where applicable
- [ ] No hardcoded paths (use `pathlib` or relative paths)

### Content Review

- [ ] Content is original synthesis (zero-copy policy)
- [ ] LLM engineering concepts are explained before code implementation
- [ ] Citations included for definitions and theorems
- [ ] Prompt templates properly formatted with metadata
